race.comment: TRINITY'S D'ORO (9) has been beaten a whisker three times since the Moe win. Has a handy 2kg claim and has the early speed to clear the awkward barrier. Nicely placed to go one better. RICKY RUNS (3) is close to breaking through, and 12 days ago was beaten a whisker over this trip at Ararat. Fitter again and is a live chance. TWINKLE VAN WINKLE (12) didn't get into it off a wide gate at Tatura (vet cleared) but had been building nicely prior. Has a low gate today and she can't be ruled out. DOUGAL MCKEEN (5) found more like his best beaten a short head at Traralgon over 1430m. Holding that form would be in the finish and has been kept on the fresh side. BOOKMAN (4) shouldn't be underestimated and won't be far away.
